# GLM Coding Plan worker lane — CURRENTLY BLOCKED SERVER-SIDE (2026-07-09).
#
# Verified by header bisection with curl: https://api.z.ai/api/anthropic
# serves this key normally (200 on messages, streaming, tools, big prompts,
# count_tokens, models), but any request carrying Claude Code's fingerprint —
# the literal header `x-app: cli` OR any claude-code anthropic-beta token —
# gets 429 error code 1302 ("rate limit reached"). Identical request with
# `x-app: sdk` or no fingerprint: 200. The same key works fine on the
# OpenAI-compatible coding endpoint (api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4), so the
# plan quota is NOT exhausted; z.ai's gateway is throttling the Claude Code
# lane for this key specifically. Also measured: concurrency > 3 on the
# anthropic endpoint returns 529 code 1305.
#
# Until z.ai unblocks (check the console for a Claude Code activation step,
# or retry later), the campaign worker uses the Kimi lane instead:
# config/klein-flux2-worker-kimi.env (see its .example).
#
# To swap back: point worker.env_files at this file and set worker.model to
# "glm-5.2" in config/klein-flux2.json, then re-run the smoke test:
#   set -a; source config/klein-flux2-worker.env; set +a
#   claude -p "Say READY and stop." --model glm-5.2 --output-format stream-json --verbose | tail -2

ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://api.z.ai/api/anthropic
ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=<your Z.ai coding-plan API key>

# If the endpoint rejects the --model name from the campaign config, uncomment
# and use these instead (Z.ai maps default model names server-side):
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=glm-5.2
# ANTHROPIC_SMALL_FAST_MODEL=glm-4.7-flash
